verses.text:
Jesus, remember me, As thou hast promised, Lord;
I said and are my Savior here?, Just tell me sing thy word;
I trust their love mine, And let me sing with glee;
Jesus, remember me, Jesus, remember me.

When I forsake thee, Lord, And sin thy dear face away,
Here will I hide my thinking face, While thy dear mercy open;
Then soon I'll sing thy praise, When my dear Jesus came;
Jesus, remember me, Jesus, remember me.
